Hi all! The contents of this archive is (c) 1992 Chris Perigo, images herein are Copywritten Freeware - this means that you can copy and distribute them, but not alter them or claim them as your own.

This archive should contain this text file and two 8 colour IFF files.

The pictures were created on an accelerated Amiga 1500 using Real3D and were boiled down to eight colours using Art Dpt. I then cropped and saved them as brushes out of Dpaint so as to cheat Telecom out of any money spent downloading blank backgrounds.

They work quite nicely as brushes if you load them into a Dpaint hi-res environment. You could import them as lo-res pictures and scroll around them although they start to look really shabby this close up.

As you can imagine they both look a lot better in their original 24 bit 1280x1024 format but my finances wouldn't stand uploading them at 1200 baud and I'm actually very pleased and suprised at how well they've held up considering the loss of resolution and colour depth.

O.K. So I know the world and his dog have done pictures of the enterprise but I'd never done one and I haven't seen it done using Real3D.

